 everyday life including polyurethanes paints and coatings adhesives sealants artificial leathers food and flavor additives cosmetics and personal care products biodegradable plastics nylons industrial lubricants phthalatefree plasticizers dyes  pigments and pharmaceutical compounds read more about a renewable building blockthat can be used to make a wide range of products succinic acid is the core product produced by bioamber succinic acid can be used to make a broad range of products found in everyday life including polyurethanes paints and coatings adhesives sealants artificial leathers food and flavor additives cosmetics and personal care products biodegradable plastics nylons industrial lubricants phthalatefree plasticizers dyes  pigments and pharmaceutical compounds back to top biobased butanediol a green version of a widely used chemical that is more sustainable bioamber can transform its biobased succinic acid into butanediol bdo and tetrahydrofuran thf in a single catalytic step bdo and thf are used to make engineering plastics polyurethanes biodegradable polyesters spandex and other specialty chemicals we make exactly the same chemical it is a straight drop in for existing bdo and thf consumers but is biobased rather than being petroleum based providing the products made with our bdo and thf a better environmental footprint read more about biobased butanediol back to top biobaseddisodiumsuccinate an all natural seasoning and flavor enhancer for use in foods bioamber biobased disodium succinate is an important ingredient of complex seasoning agents that can be used as an alternative for flavor enhancement and salt replacement for its production bioambers natural flavor grade biobased succinic acid is neutralized and spray dried to a tight particle size distribution this natural ingredient can be used with other flavors and enhancers to either intensify flavor or soften stimulating strong tastes it has good water solubility and high penetration and as a result these effects are accelerated bioamber’s biobased disodium succinate is an anhydrous powder with low particle size making it ideal for blending in dry seasonings read more about biobaseddisodiumsuccinate back to top sustainability life cycle analysis a carbon neutral footprint bioamber is committed to producing chemicals in a more environmentally responsible manner by using renewable feedstock eliminating green house gas emissions and substantially reducing energy consumption we are practicing greener chemistry that is sustainable when our sarnia plant begins production in  it will have an impressive carbon footprint relative to the existing method of producing succinic acid from petroleum our biobased process for making succinic acid will result in a  reduction in green house gas emissions and a  reduction in energy consumption an independent life cycle analysis which evaluated the entire production chain from the planting and harvesting of corn through to the purification of succinic acid revealed that net green house gas emissions for our entire process is zero this represents a  reduction relative to the  tons of greenhouse gases that are emitted per ton of succinic acid produced using the petroleum process at full capacity  tons of succinic acid per year our sarnia facility will reduce green house gas emissions by over  tons per year relative to the petroleum process this is the equivalent of taking  cars off the road each year the life cycle analysis also revealed that our entire process corn to succinic uses  less energy than the petroleumderived process a savings of over  trillion btus per year that is the equivalent to the energy consumed by  us homes annually read more about sustainability life cycle analysis back to top sustainability feedstock development feedstock flexibility bioamber is focused on using the most abundant low cost sugar available but we are also conscious of the need to be as sustainable as possible today north american corn offers the most competitively priced sugar making our succinic acid even more cost competitive we can also use sugar from cane beets sorghum wheat and tapioca to produce succinic acid our longerterm goal is to move to agricultural forestry and eventually industrial waste as alternatives to traditional sugars while these second and third generation sugars are not commercially available today bioamber is working to ensure it has the flexibility to move to these alternative feedstocks when they become economical and available in commercial quantities our proprietary yeast developed with cargill has the ability to efficiently consume xylose the principal sugar that is obtained from hemicellulose a major component of agricultural and forestry waste we are actively screening sugars produced by various new technologies in an effort to determine those that will offer legitimate alternatives to first generation sugars we are also engaged in a research program with canada’s national research counsel that is developing a new organism that can consume methane or methanol instead of sugar and produce succinic acid methane and methanol are expected to be widely available and inexpensive byproducts of the shale gas boom read more about feedstock flexibility back to top download safety data sheets sds  esds sarnia canada inventory pomacle france inventory biobased succinic acid north america documents sds  acide succinique biosourcé français sds  ácido succínico biológico español sds  biobased succinic acid english europe documents esds  biobernsteinsäure deutsch esds  biobased succinic acid english esds  acido succinico di origine biologica italiano esds  acido succinico de base biológica español esds  acide succinique biosourcé français asia documents sds     traditional chinese sds  바이오 숙신산 한국어  korean sds     simplified chinese biobased disodium succinate north america document sds  biobased disodium succinate english europe documents esds  succinato disódico de base biológica español 